The issue is that the definition of scam is not representative of the project when we are specifically talking about Logan. Scam involves as a requirement having a gain of some sort. It can not be a scam if you didn't end up having any gain from said project. And we all know (even Coffeezilla acknowledged) that Logan himself has not sold any of his zoo tokens and as such has not made any income from the project. At all. Like literally 0. In fact, he most likely lost money for this project. So despite both sentences: "Logan is the creator and frontman of the Cryptozoo project" AND "Cryptozoo is a scam" are factually correct and indisputable. It still is not correct to say that Logan scammed people with Cryptozoo. Because that implies it was Logan to actually scam people, which is also factually wrong when we previously established the two concepts above.
